{
  "text": "In Department of Pulmonology of Pediatric Clinic, the most utilised antibiotic was Procaine penicillin. Sestina et al. [CITATION_1] showed that in hospitalised paediatric patients in Birmingham the most frequently used antibiotic was co-amoxiclav while in Riga ampicillin and amoxicillin were most commonly used. This difference in practice is interesting as in most cases these narrow-spectrum agents provide sufficient cover for the majority of pathogens associated with community acquired pneumonia.",
